 📊 Key Insights

* Smoking significantly increases insurance charges
* Higher BMI is associated with higher medical costs
* Age has a positive correlation with insurance charges
* Linear Regression provides a reasonable baseline model


 📈 Results

* The model successfully predicts insurance charges with acceptable error margins
* Smoking status emerged as the most influential feature

